  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-02 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across five flow-speed operating points. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels under the accepted decision. One validation result — the most narratively detailed, covering the full five-point experimental hemolysis campaign — omits its structured prov:wasGeneratedBy activity link; the prose description of the experimental protocol and CFD comparison procedure may appear to a reviewer to substitute for the structured provenance reference, but the machine-readable generation activity is absent.",
