      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/hemolysis-5pt-campaign",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Five-point experimental hemolysis validation campaign — FDA generic centrifugal pump",
      "description": "The primary validation result for COU2. Experimental hemolysis index (HI) measurements were collected at five operating points (Q = 3, 4, 5, 6, 7 L/min at 3500 RPM) using the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump in a closed-loop flow circuit with bovine blood at 37 °C, haematocrit 33 ± 2 %. Each operating point was replicated six times across three independent test days to characterise aleatory variability. CFD predictions using the modified Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model were post-processed along Lagrangian particle trajectories seeded uniformly at the pump inlet. Monte Carlo sampling (n = 2000) over uncertain model coefficients α, β, and C propagated epistemic uncertainty into predicted HI distributions. Predicted 95th-percentile HI values fell below the absolute clinical threshold of 0.8 % at all five operating points. Normalised root-mean-square error across the five-point comparison was 14.3 %, within the pre-specified acceptance criterion of ≤ 20 %. The narrative documentation of the experimental protocol, CFD post-processing pipeline, and statistical comparison procedure is provided in the supporting technical report (DOI: 10.5281/zenodo.9900123). NOTE: the structured prov:wasGeneratedBy activity link to the generation activity record has not been populated in this result object; the prose above describes the generating process in sufficient detail that a reviewer may not notice the missing machine-readable provenance reference.",
